:"1315","1325":"1325","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1392":"1392","about 1342":"circa 1342","Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Ierland","Clanricarde, Galway, Connacht, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Ierland"},"en":{"1325–":"1325–Deceased","1315–Male":"1315–Deceased","1342–1392":"1342–1392","1325–Female":"1325–Deceased","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1392":"1392","about 1342":"about 1342","Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland","Clanricarde, Galway, Connacht, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Madden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: from Gaelic <b>Ó Madáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Madán</i>’, a shortened form of <i>Madadhán</i>, from <i>madadh</i> ‘dog’ (compare   Madigan  ).","Welsh: from the personal name <i>Madin</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Maddin","meanings":["Irish: variant of Irish   Madden  ."]},{"name":"Madigan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Conor.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Madagáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Madagán</i>’, from <i>Madadhán</i>, a personal name meaning ‘little dog’."]},{"name":"Madding","meanings":["Probably Irish: variant of   Madden  ."]},{"name":"Meddings","meanings":["Welsh and English: variant of <b>Medding</b>, itself apparently a variant of   Madden   2."]}]},{"name":"Murtogh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Ciaran, Declan, Eamon, Eamonn, Fintan, Maeve.","Irish:","midland Anglicized form of <b>Ó Muircheartaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muircheartach</i>’ a personal name meaning ‘navigator’; compare   Moriarty   in Munster. See also Scottish   Murdoch  . Variants with a final <i>-ie</i> or <i>-y</i> may also be shortened forms of   McMurdie   etc., from the same personal name."],"variants":[{"name":"Moriarty","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Liam, Seamus, Aidan, Bridie, Caitlin, Dermot, Fergus, Paddy.","Irish (Kerry): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muircheartaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muircheartach</i>’, a personal name from <i>muir</i> ‘sea’ + <i>ceardach</i> ‘skilled’, i.e. ‘skilled navigator’. A Meath and Monaghan name of the same form in Irish is Anglicized as   Murtagh  , comparable to Scottish   Murdoch  . It may also be a shortened form of Gaelic <b>Mac Muircheartaigh</b> ‘son of <i>Muircheartach</i>’, see   McMurdie  ."]},{"name":"Murtaugh","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Murtagh  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Murtha","meanings":["New Testament name, of Aramaic rather than Hebrew origin, meaning ‘lady’. It was borne by the sister of Lazarus and Mary of Bethany (John 11:1). According to Luke 10:38, when Jesus visited the house of Mary and Martha, Mary sat at his feet, listening to him, while Martha ‘was cumbered about much serving’, so that she complained to Jesus, ‘Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone?’ For this reason, the name <i>Martha</i> has always been associated with hard domestic work, as opposed to the contemplative life."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Murtogh O'Madden was born in 1325, in Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland. She married Murtogh O'Madden of Sil Anmchadha in 1340, in Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1325–":"1325–Surnud","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1342–1392":"1342–1392","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1392":"1392","about 1342":"umbes 1342","Clanricarde, County Galway, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Iirimaa","Clanricarde, Galway, Connacht, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1325–":"1325–Kuollut","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","1342–1392":"1342–1392","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollu